<br>
Case in point, I've used it in 2 different instances lately. First was a 1 group chardok king/queen raid. We had pally, cleric, shaman, mage, ranger and hmm something else, no evacer. After we got done with king and queen, we didn't feel like fighting all the way back up to get out. I got 300pp from the cash we got that day and used talisman to gate our 3 melee out. <br>
<br>
Second is I'm in a guild that hasn't been in ToV since luclin came out pretty much, and i was still missing stuff to complete some PoM flowers. PoM is not a very practical place to be bound at if you don't have mean to port out. I got a CoH from another guild and bound myself there, and I use talisman when I want to get out. That way I've been able to stay bound in PoM for a long period of time without it interfering with my normal raiding activities. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721">Woon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/">&lt;TDE&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
